{
  "texts": [
    "These may include numerical weather prediction models, climate models, hydrological models, and environmental impact assessment tools.",
    "The latter generates data utilized for research, predictions, scenario simulations, and policy decision-making.",
    "The accessibility of this information varies depending on location and the type of information required.",
    "It can be sourced from locally developed or institution-specific models, publicly available repositories, or served systems provided by research institutions, governmental bodies, or international organizations.",
    "Institutions dedicated to scientific research and meteorological or environmental monitoring often curate and disseminate these datasets to promote scientific knowledge."
  ]
}